{"type":"message","id":"0ee29201","parentId":"861ce7fd","timestamp":"2026-04-11T03:30:34.198Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d3yifrpdwycbbpykgok7lo8e","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"April 11 2026 global conflict India impact oil prices travel middle east iran pakistan china\",\n  \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n  \"model\": \"gemini-2.5-flash\",\n  \"tookMs\": 19095,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"content\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1a2ec57a7124b002\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nA significant global conflict, referred to as the \\\"2026 Iran war,\\\" has been ongoing since February 28, 2026, primarily involving the United States, Israel, and Iran. This conflict escalated following joint US-Israeli airstrikes on Iran, which led to Iranian retaliation targeting Israel, US bases, and US allies in the Middle East. A critical development in this conflict was Iran's closure of the Strait of Hormuz in early March 2026, a vital chokepoint for global oil and liquefied natural gas (LNG) shipments.\\n\\nAs of April 11, 2026, a two-week ceasefire, mediated by Pakistan, was announced on April 8, 2026, leading to scheduled talks between the US and Iran in Islamabad. However, the ceasefire is considered fragile, with reports of continued strikes by Israel and Iran in some areas. Iran has also set conditions for the peace talks, including a ceasefire in Lebanon and the unfreezing of Iranian assets.\\n\\n**Impact on Oil Prices:**\\nThe conflict and the closure of the Strait of Hormuz have caused an unprecedented shock to global oil markets. Brent crude prices surged by 10-13% to around $80-82 per barrel by March 2, 2026, and at times reached over $119 per barrel, compared to approximately $70 before the war. Analysts had sharply raised 2026 price forecasts, with Brent crude projected to average $82.85 per barrel, a nearly 30% increase from earlier forecasts. The disruption in the Strait of Hormuz is considered the primary driver of these increases, leading to acute supply shortages and heightened risks of inflation, stagflation, and recession globally. Oil prices remain volatile, with significant fluctuations reported even after the ceasefire announcement.\\n\\n**India's Impact:**\\nIndia has maintained official neutrality in the 2026 Iran War. However, the country is facing a domestic energy crisis directly linked to the conflict and the closure of the Strait of Hormuz. India, a major importer of oil from the Middle East, is experiencing soaring fuel prices and shortages of cooking gas. The Indian government has expressed concerns about the targeting of civilians and infrastructure, as well as the disruption of navigation in West Asia. The World Bank projects India's growth to slow to 6.6% in FY27 due to higher energy prices and supply chain disruptions caused by the Middle East conflict, though it remains one of the fastest-growing major economies.\\n\\n**Travel in the Middle East:**\\nThe ongoing hostilities have severely impacted air travel in the Middle East. The European Union Aviation Safety Agency (EASA) extended its advisory against flights in most Middle Eastern and Gulf airspace until at least April 24, 2026, citing continuing military escalation and risks to civil aviation. This advisory covers Bahrain, Iran, Iraq, Israel, Jordan, Kuwait, Lebanon, Oman, Qatar, the UAE, and parts of Saudi Arabia. Airlines have been forced to reroute flights, leading to longer journeys, higher fuel costs, and constantly shifting schedules. Some airports, like Baghdad International, tentatively resumed flights after weeks of closure, while Ben Gurion International in Israel remains heavily restricted. The US Embassy in Baghdad has also issued a \\\"Level 4: Do Not Travel\\\" warning for Iraq, advising against air travel within the country due to the risk of missiles, drones, and rockets. Indian carriers like Air India and IndiGo also issued travel advisories for flights to destinations such as Dubai, Jeddah, and Abu Dhabi.\\n\\n**Iran's Role:**\\nIran is a central belligerent in the current conflict, having responded to US-Israeli airstrikes with its own missile and drone attacks. Iran's closure of the Strait of Hormuz has been a key factor in the global energy crisis. Iran is currently engaged in fragile ceasefire talks with the US, mediated by Pakistan, and has put forward conditions for these negotiations. Iran is also reported to be using its control over the Strait of Hormuz to push for unprecedented transit fees from vessels.\\n\\n**Pakistan's Role:**\\nPakistan has emerged as a significant mediator in the US-Iran conflict, leveraging its ties with both Washington and Tehran. Pakistan brokered the two-week ceasefire agreement announced on April 8, 2026, and is hosting the high-level peace talks in Islamabad. Pakistan's involvement is driven by its shared border with Iran, economic reliance on oil flowing through the Strait of Hormuz, and concerns about regional instability.\\n\\n**China's Role:**\\nChina has adopted a position of cautious balancing in the conflict. While avoiding direct military intervention, China has been actively involved in diplomatic efforts, including vetoing a UN Security Council Resolution on the Strait of Hormuz crisis and supporting Pakistan's mediation efforts. China is seen as indirectly benefiting from the conflict by potentially diverting American resources and attention away from other regions. Economically, China relies heavily on oil and LNG exports from the Middle East, with a significant portion transiting the Strait of Hormuz. China's economic stability is also a factor in its desire for de-escalation, as a prolonged conflict could severely impact its exports and access to vital imports. China has also maintained economic and political support for Iran, notably through oil purchases.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1a2ec57a7124b002\\\">>>\",\n  \"citations\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2026_Iran_war\",\n      \"title\": \"wikipedia.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.britannica.com/event/2026-Iran-war\",\n      \"title\": \"britannica.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://commonslibrary.parliament.uk/research-briefings/cbp-10521/\",\n      \"title\": \"parliament.uk\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2026_Iran_war_fuel_crisis\",\n      \"title\": \"wikipedia.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.crestwoodadvisors.com/april-2026-economic-and-market-update-geopolitics-at-the-forefront/\",\n      \"title\": \"crestwoodadvisors.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/topstories/nation/983455/live-updates-conflict-in-the-middle-east-april-11-2026/story/\",\n      \"title\": \"gmanetwork.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/iran-israel-us-war-west-asia-conflict-live-updates-on-april-11-2026/article70850012.ece\",\n      \"title\": \"thehindu.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.jpost.com/middle-east/article-892374\",\n      \"title\": \"jpost.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://english.news.cn/20260409/a6d8253f2d454f409ca259408ca9bbd8/c.html\",\n      \"title\": \"news.cn\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://intellectia.ai/blog/us-iran-ceasefire-stock-market-rally-oil-prices-april-2026\",\n      \"title\": \"intellectia.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan_in_the_2026_Iran_war\",\n      \"title\": \"wikipedia.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.timesofisrael.com/pakistan-emerges-as-a-key-international-player-as-it-mediates-between-us-and-iran/\",\n      \"title\": \"timesofisrael.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.dawn.com/news/1990654/global-growth-to-suffer-due-to-war-wb-chief\",\n      \"title\": \"dawn.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/us-stocks/news/global-market-oil-shockwave-iran-conflict-triggers-record-surge-in-2026-price-forecasts/articleshow/129940954.cms?from=mdr\",\n      \"title\": \"economictimes.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.latimes.com/business/story/2026-04-10/stocks-drift-lower-oil-prices-ease-ahead-of-planned-u-s-iran-talks\",\n      \"title\": \"latimes.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.fool.com/investing/2026/04/08/xomcvx-how-volatile-oil-prices-and-global-tensions/\",\n      \"title\": \"fool.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India_in_the_2026_Iran_war\",\n      \"title\": \"wikipedia.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.worldbank.org/en/news/press-release/2026/04/09/india-remains-among-the-fastest-growing-economies\",\n      \"title\": \"worldbank.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.getaway.co.za/travel-news/middle-east-flight-disruption-2026-airports/\",\n      \"title\": \"getaway.co.za\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.aa.com.tr/en/economy/eu-aviation-safety-agency-extends-advisory-against-flights-in-most-middle-east-gulf-airspace-until-april-24/3899395\",\n      \"title\": \"aa.com.tr\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://english.alarabiya.net/business/aviation-and-transport/2026/04/09/eu-aviation-regulator-extends-warning-to-avoid-middle-east-airspace-until-april-24\",\n      \"title\": \"alarabiya.net\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://iq.usembassy.gov/security-alert-u-s-embassy-baghdad-iraq-april-8-2026/\",\n      \"title\": \"usembassy.gov\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.livemint.com/news/world/air-india-and-indigo-issue-travel-advisory-for-dubai-jeddah-and-abu-dhabi-flights-on-7-april-2026-11775519578751.html\",\n      \"title\": \"livemint.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.eurasiareview.com/11042026-the-iran-war-and-the-unravelling-of-order-in-the-middle-east-analysis/\",\n      \"title\": \"eurasiareview.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.thefridaytimes.com/10-Apr-2026/rise-pakistan-diplomatic-intermediary-global-crises\",\n      \"title\": \"thefridaytimes.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://moderndiplomacy.eu/2026/04/06/as-the-u-s-and-israel-drain-what-role-can-china-and-russia-play-in-stopping-the-war/\",\n      \"title\": \"moderndiplomacy.eu\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.lowyinstitute.org/the-interpreter/iran-crisis-puts-china-s-un-diplomacy-test\",\n      \"title\": \"lowyinstitute.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.fmprc.gov.cn/eng/xw/fyrbt/202604/t20260407_11887704.html\",\n      \"title\": \"fmprc.gov.cn\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.thecipherbrief.com/iran-china-great-power-contest\",\n      \"title\": \"thecipherbrief.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"April 11 2026 global conflict India impact oil prices travel middle east iran pakistan china","provider":"gemini","model":"gemini-2.5-flash","tookMs":19095,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"gemini","wrapped":true},"content":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1a2ec57a7124b002\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nA significant global conflict, referred to as the \"2026 Iran war,\" has been ongoing since February 28, 2026, primarily involving the United States, Israel, and Iran. This conflict escalated following joint US-Israeli airstrikes on Iran, which led to Iranian retaliation targeting Israel, US bases, and US allies in the Middle East. A critical development in this conflict was Iran's closure of the Strait of Hormuz in early March 2026, a vital chokepoint for global oil and liquefied natural gas (LNG) shipments.\n\nAs of April 11, 2026, a two-week ceasefire, mediated by Pakistan, was announced on April 8, 2026, leading to scheduled talks between the US and Iran in Islamabad. However, the ceasefire is considered fragile, with reports of continued strikes by Israel and Iran in some areas. Iran has also set conditions for the peace talks, including a ceasefire in Lebanon and the unfreezing of Iranian assets.\n\n**Impact on Oil Prices:**\nThe conflict and the closure of the Strait of Hormuz have caused an unprecedented shock to global oil markets. Brent crude prices surged by 10-13% to around $80-82 per barrel by March 2, 2026, and at times reached over $119 per barrel, compared to approximately $70 before the war. Analysts had sharply raised 2026 price forecasts, with Brent crude projected to average $82.85 per barrel, a nearly 30% increase from earlier forecasts. The disruption in the Strait of Hormuz is considered the primary driver of these increases, leading to acute supply shortages and heightened risks of inflation, stagflation, and recession globally. Oil prices remain volatile, with significant fluctuations reported even after the ceasefire announcement.\n\n**India's Impact:**\nIndia has maintained official neutrality in the 2026 Iran War. However, the country is facing a domestic energy crisis directly linked to the conflict and the closure of the Strait of Hormuz. India, a major importer of oil from the Middle East, is experiencing soaring fuel prices and shortages of cooking gas. The Indian government has expressed concerns about the targeting of civilians and infrastructure, as well as the disruption of navigation in West Asia. The World Bank projects India's growth to slow to 6.6% in FY27 due to higher energy prices and supply chain disruptions caused by the Middle East conflict, though it remains one of the fastest-growing major economies.\n\n**Travel in the Middle East:**\nThe ongoing hostilities have severely impacted air travel in the Middle East. The European Union Aviation Safety Agency (EASA) extended its advisory against flights in most Middle Eastern and Gulf airspace until at least April 24, 2026, citing continuing military escalation and risks to civil aviation. This advisory covers Bahrain, Iran, Iraq, Israel, Jordan, Kuwait, Lebanon, Oman, Qatar, the UAE, and parts of Saudi Arabia. Airlines have been forced to reroute flights, leading to longer journeys, higher fuel costs, and constantly shifting schedules. Some airports, like Baghdad International, tentatively resumed flights after weeks of closure, while Ben Gurion International in Israel remains heavily restricted. The US Embassy in Baghdad has also issued a \"Level 4: Do Not Travel\" warning for Iraq, advising against air travel within the country due to the risk of missiles, drones, and rockets. Indian carriers like Air India and IndiGo also issued travel advisories for flights to destinations such as Dubai, Jeddah, and Abu Dhabi.\n\n**Iran's Role:**\nIran is a central belligerent in the current conflict, having responded to US-Israeli airstrikes with its own missile and drone attacks. Iran's closure of the Strait of Hormuz has been a key factor in the global energy crisis. Iran is currently engaged in fragile ceasefire talks with the US, mediated by Pakistan, and has put forward conditions for these negotiations. Iran is also reported to be using its control over the Strait of Hormuz to push for unprecedented transit fees from vessels.\n\n**Pakistan's Role:**\nPakistan has emerged as a significant mediator in the US-Iran conflict, leveraging its ties with both Washington and Tehran. Pakistan brokered the two-week ceasefire agreement announced on April 8, 2026, and is hosting the high-level peace talks in Islamabad. Pakistan's involvement is driven by its shared border with Iran, economic reliance on oil flowing through the Strait of Hormuz, and concerns about regional instability.\n\n**China's Role:**\nChina has adopted a position of cautious balancing in the conflict. While avoiding direct military intervention, China has been actively involved in diplomatic efforts, including vetoing a UN Security Council Resolution on the Strait of Hormuz crisis and supporting Pakistan's mediation efforts. China is seen as indirectly benefiting from the conflict by potentially diverting American resources and attention away from other regions. Economically, China relies heavily on oil and LNG exports from the Middle East, with a significant portion transiting the Strait of Hormuz. China's economic stability is also a factor in its desire for de-escalation, as a prolonged conflict could severely impact its exports and access to vital imports. China has also maintained economic and political support for Iran, notably through oil purchases.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1a2ec57a7124b002\">>>","citations":[{"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2026_Iran_war","title":"wikipedia.org"},{"url":"https://www.britannica.com/event/2026-Iran-war","title":"britannica.com"},{"url":"https://commonslibrary.parliament.uk/research-briefings/cbp-10521/","title":"parliament.uk"},{"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2026_Iran_war_fuel_crisis","title":"wikipedia.org"},{"url":"https://www.crestwoodadvisors.com/april-2026-economic-and-market-update-geopolitics-at-the-forefront/","title":"crestwoodadvisors.com"},{"url":"https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/topstories/nation/983455/live-updates-conflict-in-the-middle-east-april-11-2026/story/","title":"gmanetwork.com"},{"url":"https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/iran-israel-us-war-west-asia-conflict-live-updates-on-april-11-2026/article70850012.ece","title":"thehindu.com"},{"url":"https://www.jpost.com/middle-east/article-892374","title":"jpost.com"},{"url":"https://english.news.cn/20260409/a6d8253f2d454f409ca259408ca9bbd8/c.html","title":"news.cn"},{"url":"https://intellectia.ai/blog/us-iran-ceasefire-stock-market-rally-oil-prices-april-2026","title":"intellectia.ai"},{"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan_in_the_2026_Iran_war","title":"wikipedia.org"},{"url":"https://www.timesofisrael.com/pakistan-emerges-as-a-key-international-player-as-it-mediates-between-us-and-iran/","title":"timesofisrael.com"},{"url":"https://www.dawn.com/news/1990654/global-growth-to-suffer-due-to-war-wb-chief","title":"dawn.com"},{"url":"https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/us-stocks/news/global-market-oil-shockwave-iran-conflict-triggers-record-surge-in-2026-price-forecasts/articleshow/129940954.cms?from=mdr","title":"economictimes.com"},{"url":"https://www.latimes.com/business/story/2026-04-10/stocks-drift-lower-oil-prices-ease-ahead-of-planned-u-s-iran-talks","title":"latimes.com"},{"url":"https://www.fool.com/investing/2026/04/08/xomcvx-how-volatile-oil-prices-and-global-tensions/","title":"fool.com"},{"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India_in_the_2026_Iran_war","title":"wikipedia.org"},{"url":"https://www.worldbank.org/en/news/press-release/2026/04/09/india-remains-among-the-fastest-growing-economies","title":"worldbank.org"},{"url":"https://www.getaway.co.za/travel-news/middle-east-flight-disruption-2026-airports/","title":"getaway.co.za"},{"url":"https://www.aa.com.tr/en/economy/eu-aviation-safety-agency-extends-advisory-against-flights-in-most-middle-east-gulf-airspace-until-april-24/3899395","title":"aa.com.tr"},{"url":"https://english.alarabiya.net/business/aviation-and-transport/2026/04/09/eu-aviation-regulator-extends-warning-to-avoid-middle-east-airspace-until-april-24","title":"alarabiya.net"},{"url":"https://iq.usembassy.gov/security-alert-u-s-embassy-baghdad-iraq-april-8-2026/","title":"usembassy.gov"},{"url":"https://www.livemint.com/news/world/air-india-and-indigo-issue-travel-advisory-for-dubai-jeddah-and-abu-dhabi-flights-on-7-april-2026-11775519578751.html","title":"livemint.com"},{"url":"https://www.eurasiareview.com/11042026-the-iran-war-and-the-unravelling-of-order-in-the-middle-east-analysis/","title":"eurasiareview.com"},{"url":"https://www.thefridaytimes.com/10-Apr-2026/rise-pakistan-diplomatic-intermediary-global-crises","title":"thefridaytimes.com"},{"url":"https://moderndipl